    • #Newline

  • Did you know: Astronomers have detected unusually high quantities of carbon#Comma the basis of all terrestrial life#Comma in an infant solar system around nearby star Beta Pictoris#Comma 63 light-years away.

  • Giant structures stretching more than a billion light years across have been revealed by two new maps of the distribution of galaxies in the universe. The updated atlases lend more support to the idea that the universe is dominated by dark matter and dark energy.
    • #Newline
  • On January 28#Comma 1986#Comma a ruptured O-ring in the right solid rocket booster caused the Space Shuttle Challenger to explode soon after launch.
    • #Newline
  • The latest new cosmic map is a three-dimensional atlas of more than one million galaxies reaching a distance greater than 5 billion light-years. The most distant galaxies in the universe are more than 13 billion light-years away#Comma and not all of them have been catalogued or even discovered. The map was created using a new artificial intelligence technique that helps overcome challenges to figuring out how far galaxies are in a photograph that renders them all essentially in two dimensions.   • Did you know: two giant black holes have been found just 24 light years apart. The previous closest pair of black holes were 4500 light years apart.
    • #Newline

    • #Newline
